(26), 52(29), 52(29), 55(27), 47(27), 27(12), respectively.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1437,151,1463]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis box="[199,427,830,855]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Macropterous male:</emphasis>
Similar to female in both colouration and structure, but slightly smaller. Pore plate (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 88–94" captionStartId="37.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1927]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,193,1927]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURES 88–94. Holopothrips flavisetis sp. nov. holotype and paratypes. (88) head and pronotum; (89) mesonotum; (90) metanotum; (91) body; (92) pelta; (93) pore plate on abdominal sternite VIII (white arrow); (94) spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1445208/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 93</figureCitation>
) with punctuate texture and present on sternite VIII, faint irregular median spots posterior to discal setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1437,151,1463]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis box="[199,690,902,927]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
